# Generation 5: variable queries resolved by unification over the facts.
> socrates is a man
< Learned: man(socrates).
> plato is a man
< Learned: man(plato).
> aristotle is a man
< Learned: man(aristotle).
# "who is a X?" binds the variable to every matching subject, in order.
> who is a man?
< socrates, plato, aristotle.
# "what is a X?" works the same way.
> rex is a dog
< Learned: dog(rex).
> what is a dog?
< rex.
# Predicate never mentioned -> "I don't know" (gen16), distinct from a known
# predicate with no members ("Nobody that I know of.").
> who is a robot?
< I don't know about robot.
# Ground query still works (no regression).
> is socrates a man?
< Yes.
